<form theme="dark" version="1.1">
  <label>Service Overview</label>
  <fieldset submitButton="false">
    <input type="text" token="index">
      <label>Index</label>
      <default>service_reliability_test</default>
    </input>
    <input type="time">
      <label>Time Range</label>
      <default>
        <earliest>0</earliest>
        <latest></latest>
      </default>
    </input>
  </fieldset>
  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>Overall Service Availability (%)</title>
      <single>
        <search>
          <query>`svc_availability($index$)`
            | stats avg(availability_pct) AS availability</query>
          <earliest>$earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$latest$</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="colorMode">none</option>
        <option name="drilldown">none</option>
        <option name="height">183</option>
        <option name="numberPrecision">0.00</option>
        <option name="rangeColors">["0xd41f1f","0xf1813f","0x53a051"]</option>
        <option name="rangeValues">[70,90]</option>
        <option name="unit">%</option>
        <option name="useColors">1</option>
      </single>
    </panel>
    <panel>
      <title>Average Stability Score (0–100)</title>
      <single>
        <search>
          <query>`svc_reliability_score($index$)`
            | stats avg(reliability_score) AS stability</query>
          <earliest>$earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$latest$</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="drilldown">none</option>
        <option name="height">180</option>
        <option name="numberPrecision">0.00</option>
        <option name="rangeColors">["0xdc4e41","0xf1813f","0x118832"]</option>
        <option name="rangeValues">[60,85]</option>
        <option name="unit">%</option>
        <option name="useColors">1</option>
      </single>
    </panel>
  </row>
  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>Top Unstable Services</title>
      <table>
        <title>Services exhibiting statistically abnormal failure spikes compared to their historical baseline.</title>
        <search>
          <query>`svc_instability($index$)`
            | where unstable=1
            | stats count AS instability_events BY service
            | sort - instability_events</query>
          <earliest>$earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$latest$</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="drilldown">cell</option>
      </table>
    </panel>
  </row>
  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>Failure Rate Trend (15-Minute Intervals)</title>
      <chart>
        <title>Trend of detected failure events across services. Useful for spotting gradual degradation or sudden spikes.</title>
        <search>
          <query>`svc_failure_trend(service_reliability_test)`</query>
          <earliest>$earliest$</earliest>
          <latest>$latest$</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="charting.axisTitleX.visibility">visible</option>
        <option name="charting.axisTitleY.visibility">visible</option>
        <option name="charting.axisTitleY2.visibility">visible</option>
        <option name="charting.chart">line</option>
        <option name="charting.chart.nullValueMode">gaps</option>
        <option name="charting.chart.showDataLabels">none</option>
        <option name="charting.drilldown">none</option>
        <option name="charting.layout.splitSeries">0</option>
        <option name="charting.legend.mode">standard</option>
        <option name="charting.legend.placement">right</option>
        <option name="height">292</option>
        <option name="trellis.enabled">0</option>
      </chart>
    </panel>
  </row>
  <row>
  <panel>
    <title>How to Interpret This Dashboard</title>
    <html>
      <div>
        <h3>What This Dashboard Shows</h3>
        <p>
          This dashboard provides a high-level summary of service reliability using application and service logs.
          It is intended for quick health checks and executive-level visibility.
        </p>

        <h3>Key Metrics Explained</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><b>Service Availability (%)</b> – Percentage of log events that are not classified as failures.</li>
          <li><b>Stability Score (0–100)</b> – Higher scores indicate fewer failures and more consistent behavior.</li>
          <li><b>Top Unstable Services</b> – Services experiencing abnormal failure spikes.</li>
          <li><b>Failure Rate Trend</b> – Increasing trends indicate emerging reliability issues.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>How to Use This View</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Use this as a daily health check.</li>
          <li>If availability drops or stability score declines, drill into Instability or SLA Risk dashboards.</li>
          <li>Repeated appearance of the same service indicates chronic reliability issues.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Important Notes</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>This dashboard is log-based and does not reflect infrastructure metrics.</li>
          <li>Short outages may not significantly impact availability but will affect stability.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </html>
  </panel>
</row>
</form>